    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nPreviously, when no `width` was passed to `vim.api.nvim_open_win`, the window was equalized. After https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/19f5f05ac2b950bf68116cd0f3d08c29ee32a96d this no longer happens, and the opened window is tiny.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:lua vim.api.nvim_open_window(1, true, {split='right'})`\n3. \n\n<img width=\"1844\" height=\"1444\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4174d37c-e0ab-484d-9047-f3be2c04ba77\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe windows should be equal in size\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1379-a4006360f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 42\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.2.0-2.202510021354.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-nightly Fedora COPR",
